&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 22 MONTHS TO COVER THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen within the Audiology Service for a fixed term full-time Audiologist to assist in the provision of a high quality Audiology service to the population of North Wales served by BCUHB. The post holder will perform duties within the Adult Audiology service as described in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will be performed in outpatient, domiciliary and/or in-patient settings across the area served by BCUHB, with the base to be confirmed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be responsibility to train and supervise other clinical staff where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clinical Scientists, Audiologists and Students who are close to completing their training would all be encouraged to apply. This is an ideal opportunity to further develop clinical and service development skills in a supportive and progressive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date:9 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suzanne Tyson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Principal Audiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;suzanne.tyson@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
